com.sharneng.lookup

Interface Lookup<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the object to be looked up.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractLookup

    public interface Lookup<T>
    The primary interface to support lookup of a object by some index.

    All methods in this interface must be thread safe.

    Author:
    Kenneth Xu

      • get

        T get(@CheckForNull
    Object key)
        Find and return the reference object for given key, or return a default value when the object is not found.

        The default value is implementation dependent and must not be null.

        Parameters:
        key - the key to lookup the object
        Returns:
        the reference object found or a default value if not found
        Throws:
        LookupException - if failed to lookup the reference object and unable to provide a non null default value

      • get

        T get(@CheckForNull
    Object key,
    T defaultValue)
        Find and return the reference object for given key, or return the specified default value when the object is not found.
        Parameters:
        key - the key to lookup the object
        defaultValue - the default value to be returned if object is not found
        Returns:
        the reference object found or defaultValue if not found
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - when defaultValue is null

      • hunt

        T hunt(Object key)
        Find and return the reference object for given key, or fail if one doesn't exist.

        hunt distinguish itself from get and find methods by throwing exception when the reference object cannot be found.

        Parameters:
        key - the key to lookup the object
        Returns:
        the reference object found
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - when key is null
        LookupException - if failed to lookup the reference object
